00:30:54.040 --> 00:30:56.500 align:middle line:84%
world because the cost of
smartphones and tablets

00:30:56.500 --> 00:30:58.600 align:middle line:90%
is going to drop to $10 apiece.

00:30:58.600 --> 00:31:00.340 align:middle line:84%
What this means
is that all of us

00:31:00.340 --> 00:31:02.710 align:middle line:84%
are going to have
a backup brain.

00:31:02.710 --> 00:31:05.980 align:middle line:84%
Sugata Mitra won the
TED Prize for Education.

00:31:05.980 --> 00:31:07.650 align:middle line:90%
I once heard him speak.

00:31:07.650 --> 00:31:11.080 align:middle line:84%
And he said, the way we
educate our kids is ridiculous.

00:31:11.080 --> 00:31:14.380 align:middle line:84%
So someone asked, what do
we need to stop teaching?

00:31:14.380 --> 00:31:18.100 align:middle line:10%
And he said, stop teaching
spelling, stop teaching math,

00:31:18.100 --> 00:31:20.350 align:middle line:10%
because our kids are going
to have a backup brain that

00:31:20.350 --> 00:31:22.000 align:middle line:10%
can already do that.

00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:26.510 align:middle line:84%
Why are we teaching them skills
that were needed in 1970?

00:31:26.510 --> 00:31:28.960 align:middle line:84%
So then the question is,
what do we teach our kids?

00:31:28.960 --> 00:31:32.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, we teach our
kids transformation.

00:31:32.100 --> 00:31:34.750 align:middle line:84%
There's a difference between
learning and transformation.

00:31:34.750 --> 00:31:36.590 align:middle line:90%
Learning is facts and figures.

00:31:36.590 --> 00:31:40.630 align:middle line:84%
Learning is stuff that
you easily forget.

00:31:40.630 --> 00:31:42.890 align:middle line:90%
But transformation is different.

00:31:42.890 --> 00:31:44.540 align:middle line:84%
Transformation is
beyond learning.

00:31:44.540 --> 00:31:47.630 align:middle line:84%
Transformation is an
expansion of your world view.

00:31:47.630 --> 00:31:50.420 align:middle line:84%
And a mind, once
expanded, can never again

00:31:50.420 --> 00:31:52.430 align:middle line:90%
shrink to its original size.

00:31:52.430 --> 00:31:56.740 align:middle line:84%
Once your world view changes
where you become more authentic

00:31:56.740 --> 00:32:00.500 align:middle line:84%
or you become more
empathetic and kind

00:32:00.500 --> 00:32:04.730 align:middle line:84%
or you become more compassionate
or you become more autonomous,

00:32:04.730 --> 00:32:07.230 align:middle line:90%
you never lose that sense.

00:32:07.230 --> 00:32:12.450 align:middle line:84%
Now, philosophers and
anthropologists and professors

00:32:12.450 --> 00:32:15.420 align:middle line:84%
who study transformation
say that transformation

00:32:15.420 --> 00:32:18.220 align:middle line:84%
in the world today
comes from two things.

00:32:18.220 --> 00:32:21.000 align:middle line:84%
The first is the
disorienting dilemma.

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:22.860 align:middle line:84%
It is the setback,
the suffering,

00:32:22.860 --> 00:32:26.340 align:middle line:84%
the thing that pounds you
and knocks you off course.

00:32:26.340 --> 00:32:28.290 align:middle line:10%
But when you bounce back
from that bankruptcy

00:32:28.290 --> 00:32:30.810 align:middle line:10%
or from that broken heart
or from that divorce

00:32:30.810 --> 00:32:33.702 align:middle line:10%
or from that bout in
hospital, you are wiser,

00:32:33.702 --> 00:32:35.410 align:middle line:10%
and you see the world
in a different way,

00:32:35.410 --> 00:32:42.240 align:middle line:10%
and you know what you need to
do next to avoid that setback.

00:32:42.240 --> 00:32:43.620 align:middle line:90%
Google did a study.

00:32:43.620 --> 00:32:46.950 align:middle line:84%
This was cited in Salim Ismail's
fantastic book "Exponential

00:32:46.950 --> 00:32:48.300 align:middle line:90%
Organizations."

00:32:48.300 --> 00:32:51.660 align:middle line:84%
Google found that its
best people were not,

00:32:51.660 --> 00:32:56.490 align:middle line:84%
contrary to popular belief, STEM
graduates, but young people who

00:32:56.490 --> 00:33:00.630 align:middle line:84%
had gone through suffering and
had emerged from that suffering

00:33:00.630 --> 00:33:03.870 align:middle line:84%
humbler, kinder,
more compassionate.

00:33:03.870 --> 00:33:05.130 align:middle line:90%
Those were the best people.

00:33:05.130 --> 00:33:09.990 align:middle line:90%


00:33:09.990 --> 00:33:14.280 align:middle line:84%
Now, transformation
comes from suffering.

00:33:14.280 --> 00:33:19.740 align:middle line:84%
But it also comes from a gradual
expansion of meaning schema.

00:33:19.740 --> 00:33:22.050 align:middle line:84%
This gradual expansing
of meaning schema

00:33:22.050 --> 00:33:25.547 align:middle line:84%
is when we learn from mentors,
when we travel the world, when

00:33:25.547 --> 00:33:27.630 align:middle line:84%
we're introduced to people
who have figured it out

00:33:27.630 --> 00:33:30.480 align:middle line:84%
and they are willing to
help us figure it out,

00:33:30.480 --> 00:33:32.910 align:middle line:90%
when we wisen up.

00:33:32.910 --> 00:33:37.830 align:middle line:84%
The point of education has to
be to speed up the accumulation

00:33:37.830 --> 00:33:39.330 align:middle line:90%
of meaning schema--

00:33:39.330 --> 00:33:42.570 align:middle line:84%
in short, to speed up wisdom,
to speed up transformation

00:33:42.570 --> 00:33:44.850 align:middle line:84%
so that the human
machine doesn't

00:33:44.850 --> 00:33:47.400 align:middle line:90%
have to go through suffering.

00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:49.350 align:middle line:84%
And when we do go
through suffering,

00:33:49.350 --> 00:33:53.135 align:middle line:84%
we know how to sail past
it and see it as a lesson.

00:33:53.135 --> 00:33:54.510 align:middle line:84%
So the problem
with our education

00:33:54.510 --> 00:33:57.090 align:middle line:84%
is it isn't paying
enough attention

00:33:57.090 --> 00:34:00.630 align:middle line:84%
