00:41:44.590 --> 00:41:45.850 align:middle line:90%
actually make us miserable.

00:41:45.850 --> 00:41:48.010 align:middle line:84%
And ironically, I
live in a culture

00:41:48.010 --> 00:41:50.560 align:middle line:84%
with the inalienable
right to pursue happiness.

00:41:50.560 --> 00:41:53.230 align:middle line:90%
You cannot pursue happiness.

00:41:53.230 --> 00:41:55.810 align:middle line:90%
It's not-- it's a ramification.

00:41:55.810 --> 00:41:57.710 align:middle line:90%
Happiness is a byproduct.

00:41:57.710 --> 00:42:00.880 align:middle line:84%
So what you need to
do is sleep correctly.

00:42:00.880 --> 00:42:02.210 align:middle line:90%
Have loving relationships.

00:42:02.210 --> 00:42:03.010 align:middle line:90%
Eat well.

00:42:03.010 --> 00:42:04.460 align:middle line:90%
Get some exercise.

00:42:04.460 --> 00:42:05.690 align:middle line:90%
It's not brain surgery.

00:42:05.690 --> 00:42:07.900 align:middle line:84%
And yet, 100 million
prescriptions

00:42:07.900 --> 00:42:10.870 align:middle line:84%
for antidepressants are
written in this country

00:42:10.870 --> 00:42:12.760 align:middle line:90%
of 330 million people.

00:42:12.760 --> 00:42:15.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is an insane
time we're living in.

00:42:15.700 --> 00:42:16.840 align:middle line:90%
All of us have our phones.

00:42:16.840 --> 00:42:19.000 align:middle line:84%
Some of the times they're
under our pillows.

00:42:19.000 --> 00:42:21.190 align:middle line:84%
I don't know anyone who
doesn't go to the bathroom

00:42:21.190 --> 00:42:24.430 align:middle line:84%
without an iPad or
something in there.

00:42:24.430 --> 00:42:28.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Kids who were raised with
social media likes are already

00:42:28.660 --> 00:42:29.590 align:middle line:90%
quantized.

00:42:29.590 --> 00:42:33.910 align:middle line:84%
They're already quantifying
their understanding

00:42:33.910 --> 00:42:35.020 align:middle line:90%
of themselves.

00:42:35.020 --> 00:42:38.740 align:middle line:90%
So the problem with it is--

00:42:38.740 --> 00:42:42.100 align:middle line:84%
to me, it's almost less
about that it's specifically

00:42:42.100 --> 00:42:48.220 align:middle line:84%
social media, but that
their sense of self-worth

00:42:48.220 --> 00:42:52.930 align:middle line:84%
is external to them
rather than experiential,

00:42:52.930 --> 00:42:56.560 align:middle line:84%
that it's something telling
me how much I'm worth.

00:42:56.560 --> 00:42:59.770 align:middle line:90%
And it's not even human.

00:42:59.770 --> 00:43:02.980 align:middle line:84%
When it's a number,
then it's not actually

00:43:02.980 --> 00:43:04.990 align:middle line:90%
feeding my organism.

00:43:04.990 --> 00:43:11.260 align:middle line:84%
It's feeding some
accountant inside myself.

00:43:11.260 --> 00:43:13.750 align:middle line:84%
That might be
Wetiko right there.

00:43:13.750 --> 00:43:16.960 align:middle line:84%
That's the disease,
this quantified self.

00:43:16.960 --> 00:43:19.920 align:middle line:90%


00:43:19.920 --> 00:43:23.800 align:middle line:84%
>> How we are in the world,
how we relate to each other,

00:43:23.800 --> 00:43:27.170 align:middle line:84%
how we relate to the planet
is part of the problem.

00:43:27.170 --> 00:43:28.980 align:middle line:84%
And unless we get
to the root of that

00:43:28.980 --> 00:43:32.910 align:middle line:84%
and start to think in a more
integrated, more holistic, more

00:43:32.910 --> 00:43:36.060 align:middle line:84%
humanistic way about our
place in the order of things,

00:43:36.060 --> 00:43:38.858 align:middle line:84%
then we'll simply continue
refining a system that's

00:43:38.858 --> 00:43:41.400 align:middle line:84%
run its course, and this creates
all the problems that we now

00:43:41.400 --> 00:43:42.450 align:middle line:90%
scratch our heads about.

00:43:42.450 --> 00:43:44.310 align:middle line:90%
We've created the food crisis.

00:43:44.310 --> 00:43:45.780 align:middle line:84%
We've created the
economic crisis.

00:43:45.780 --> 00:43:47.740 align:middle line:84%
We've created the
climate crisis.

00:43:47.740 --> 00:43:49.980 align:middle line:84%
And if we're to
solve them, we have

00:43:49.980 --> 00:43:51.510 align:middle line:84%
to get even more
creative, not less.

00:43:51.510 --> 00:44:05.034 align:middle line:90%


00:44:05.034 --> 00:44:09.510 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, we justified
our competitive landscape.

00:44:09.510 --> 00:44:14.700 align:middle line:84%
We justified this
system with a kind

00:44:14.700 --> 00:44:18.750 align:middle line:84%
of a bastardized
interpretation of Darwin.

00:44:18.750 --> 00:44:21.060 align:middle line:84%
Species compete,
and one succeeds,

00:44:21.060 --> 00:44:22.900 align:middle line:84%
and that's why humans
are on the top.

00:44:22.900 --> 00:44:23.700 align:middle line:90%
We won.

00:44:23.700 --> 00:44:26.310 align:middle line:84%
We're the apex
predator, and yay.

00:44:26.310 --> 00:44:29.125 align:middle line:90%
And I looked-- I read Darwin.

00:44:29.125 --> 00:44:30.750 align:middle line:84%
And if you read
Darwin, I mean, there's

00:44:30.750 --> 00:44:33.180 align:middle line:84%
a little tiny bit
on competition.

00:44:33.180 --> 00:44:34.830 align:middle line:84%
But for the most
part, what Darwin

00:44:34.830 --> 00:44:37.500 align:middle line:84%
is marveling at
page after page is

00:44:37.500 --> 00:44:40.553 align:middle line:84%
cooperation and collaboration
between species.

00:44:40.553 --> 00:44:41.970 align:middle line:84%
But I remember the
science teacher

00:44:41.970 --> 00:44:44.100 align:middle line:84%
who taught me about
evolution and said

00:44:44.100 --> 00:44:46.680 align:middle line:84%
that the trees are competing
for sunlight in the forest.

00:44:46.680 --> 00:44:49.110 align:middle line:84%
And the big tree will
get up to the sun first,

00:44:49.110 --> 00:44:51.810 align:middle line:84%
and the little tree will be
in the shade and will die.

00:44:51.810 --> 00:44:54.270 align:middle line:10%
And I've just read this
book, "Secret Life of Trees,"

00:44:54.270 --> 00:44:55.950 align:middle line:10%
and it turns out
just the opposite,

00:44:55.950 --> 00:44:58.470 align:middle line:10%
that the big tree that's
getting the sunlight

00:44:58.470 --> 00:45:01.140 align:middle line:10%
shares its nutrients
through the soil

00:45:01.140 --> 00:45:03.570 align:middle line:10%
through a matrix of mycelia--

00:45:03.570 --> 00:45:05.280 align:middle line:10%
of mushrooms in the soil--

00:45:05.280 --> 00:45:06.630 align:middle line:10%
with the little tree.

00:45:06.630 --> 00:45:08.713 align:middle line:84%
And then the little tree
gets all those nutrients.

00:45:08.713 --> 00:45:11.250 align:middle line:84%
Then, in the winter when the
big tree loses its leaves,

00:45:11.250 --> 00:45:13.470 align:middle line:84%
the little tree, which
is usually an evergreen,

00:45:13.470 --> 00:45:16.680 align:middle line:84%
passes nutrients back
through those same mushrooms

00:45:16.680 --> 00:45:18.840 align:middle line:84%
and give the nutrients
back to the big tree.

00:45:18.840 --> 00:45:21.900 align:middle line:84%
So the two trees are
not competing for sun.

00:45:21.900 --> 00:45:23.370 align:middle line:90%
They're collaborating.

00:45:23.370 --> 00:45:27.330 align:middle line:84%
They have diverse
strategies of survival,

00:45:27.330 --> 00:45:33.420 align:middle line:84%
which allows the forest
as a collective organism

00:45:33.420 --> 00:45:35.170 align:middle line:90%
to support itself.

00:45:35.170 --> 00:45:38.280 align:middle line:10%
So if human beings are
the most advanced species

00:45:38.280 --> 00:45:40.650 align:middle line:10%
on the evolutionary
trail, it's just

00:45:40.650 --> 00:45:44.820 align:middle line:10%
a reflection of the
complexity of collaboration

00:45:44.820 --> 00:45:45.850 align:middle line:10%
that we were able to do.

00:45:45.850 --> 00:45:48.540 align:middle line:90%


00:45:48.540 --> 00:45:50.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Human beings are
very programmable.

00:45:50.340 --> 00:45:52.470 align:middle line:84%
They can be programmed
towards ideas

00:45:52.470 --> 00:45:55.380 align:middle line:84%
that unify them and
create more compassion

00:45:55.380 --> 00:45:56.500 align:middle line:90%
and love in the world.

00:45:56.500 --> 00:45:59.460 align:middle line:84%
But they can also be
programmed for ideas that

00:45:59.460 --> 00:46:01.950 align:middle line:90%
create this unity and hate.

00:46:01.950 --> 00:46:04.170 align:middle line:84%
The question is, where
is the human race going,

00:46:04.170 --> 00:46:06.570 align:middle line:90%
and what do we want to bet on?

00:46:06.570 --> 00:46:09.960 align:middle line:84%
I believe that we are moving
more and more towards unity.

00:46:09.960 --> 00:46:12.720 align:middle line:84%
And if you look at issues
like global warming,

00:46:12.720 --> 00:46:16.500 align:middle line:84%
no country on its own can
prevent global warming.

00:46:16.500 --> 00:46:19.350 align:middle line:84%
The only way to do it is to
do it as a collective species.

00:46:19.350 --> 00:46:22.110 align:middle line:84%
No country on its
own can prevent wars.

00:46:22.110 --> 00:46:24.750 align:middle line:84%
The only way to do it is to do
it as a unified human species.

00:46:24.750 --> 00:46:27.300 align:middle line:90%


00:46:27.300 --> 00:46:30.733 align:middle line:84%
>> It's not only feasible,
but it is already happening.

00:46:30.733 --> 00:46:33.150 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people are throwing
their hands up about this

00:46:33.150 --> 00:46:35.580 align:middle line:84%
and say, how can you
possibly change us?

00:46:35.580 --> 00:46:39.330 align:middle line:84%
Well, the fact is you can if you
give people a better argument,

00:46:39.330 --> 00:46:43.650 align:middle line:84%
if you open their eyes to
more profound principles

00:46:43.650 --> 00:46:45.750 align:middle line:84%
of human welfare
and flourishing,

00:46:45.750 --> 00:46:47.580 align:middle line:84%
if you persuade them
in the right way

00:46:47.580 --> 00:46:50.280 align:middle line:84%
that this is a better way to
do things and then show them

00:46:50.280 --> 00:46:52.750 align:middle line:84%
how it can be done, how
other people are doing it.

00:46:52.750 --> 00:46:55.440 align:middle line:84%
But then movements start to
happen, and they do happen.

00:46:55.440 --> 00:46:56.653 align:middle line:90%
And you can see it now.

00:46:56.653 --> 00:46:58.820 align:middle line:10%
You can see it in the
environmental world with Greta

00:46:58.820 --> 00:47:01.080 align:middle line:10%
Thunberg and the rest who are--

00:47:01.080 --> 00:47:03.150 align:middle line:10%
one person becomes
a dozen people

00:47:03.150 --> 00:47:06.270 align:middle line:10%
becomes several thousand,
and then you have a movement.

00:47:06.270 --> 00:47:09.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think, if there's
the appetite for change

00:47:09.020 --> 00:47:13.672 align:middle line:84%
and the impulse for change
and I feel it happening,

00:47:13.672 --> 00:47:14.880 align:middle line:90%
then the ideas are out there.

00:47:14.880 --> 00:47:18.390 align:middle line:84%
The practices are there
to help make it a reality.

00:47:18.390 --> 00:47:24.350 align:middle line:84%
>> First, we need to
figure out, who am I?

00:47:24.350 --> 00:47:26.600 align:middle line:84%
The most important
aspect is, how do I

00:47:26.600 --> 00:47:30.560 align:middle line:90%
move through the world as that?

00:47:30.560 --> 00:47:33.800 align:middle line:84%
And then, OK, what
is my unique way

00:47:33.800 --> 00:47:36.080 align:middle line:90%
that that's going to manifest?

00:47:36.080 --> 00:47:39.320 align:middle line:90%
Maybe I'm a school teacher.

00:47:39.320 --> 00:47:42.410 align:middle line:10%
Maybe I'm the waitress who
serves up smiles with muffins,

00:47:42.410 --> 00:47:45.910 align:middle line:10%
whatever I may be.

00:47:45.910 --> 00:47:51.970 align:middle line:84%
But that is all in service
of that higher purpose, which

00:47:51.970 --> 00:47:53.710 align:middle line:90%
is to wake up.

00:47:53.710 --> 00:47:58.420 align:middle line:84%
And so that connection to the
children, the grandchildren,

00:47:58.420 --> 00:48:02.800 align:middle line:84%
the future, to the
Earth, that connection

00:48:02.800 --> 00:48:04.970 align:middle line:90%
is what will save our species.

00:48:04.970 --> 00:48:07.510 align:middle line:84%
So whether you're talking
about personal depression,

00:48:07.510 --> 00:48:12.330 align:middle line:84%
personal addiction,
personal sense of misery,

00:48:12.330 --> 00:48:16.110 align:middle line:84%
or you're talking about
planetary destruction,

00:48:16.110 --> 00:48:19.200 align:middle line:84%
at the very core, the
answer is the same--

00:48:19.200 --> 00:48:21.190 align:middle line:90%
connection, oneness.

00:48:21.190 --> 00:48:25.690 align:middle line:90%


00:48:25.690 --> 00:48:28.740 align:middle line:90%
